content: I'm looking for some recommendations for musical theater soundtracks to listen to on my daily commute. I've been listening to Hadestown and Dear Evan Hansen a lot lately, but I want to mix it up. By the way, I just watched the film adaptation of Hamilton on Disney+ last weekend and I'm still obsessed with Renée Elise Goldsberry's rendition of "Helpless" - it's been on repeat in my head ever since!
